        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="aligh(right)"><placeName>Claiborne</placeName>
                <date>May 14 5617</date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev: Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Dear &amp; Respected sir!</p>
            <p>I am sorely grieved for not being able<lb/> to comply with my promise, in remitting
                the<lb/> subscriptions due you of last year, as also the<lb/>
                <sic>Ballance</sic> on the <add>Hebrew</add>. I have as yet not any money<lb/>
                collected, <sic>allthough</sic> having hath the promise re˶<lb/>peatedly. Gladly
                would I advance the whole<lb/> could I spare the amount. But I am &amp; have<lb/>
                been for some time past greatly <sic>embarrast</sic>,<lb/> so much so, that I am
                unable to meet my own lia˶<lb/>bilities.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Believe me, my dear sir, that I feel exceedingly<lb/> mortified, for
                not having <sic>remittet</sic> to <persName>Rev. Dr.<lb/> Lilienthal</persName> the
                Balance due him, which places you<lb/> no doubt in <sic>a</sic> unpleasant
                situation, more so, as I am<lb/> an entire stranger to you, nevertheless, you hath
                the<lb/> kindness &amp; confidence in procuring the request
                    ar˶<lb/><sic>tikles</sic>. I have written to the Chief Rabbi praying for<lb/>
                indulgence until <add>Hebrew</add>. By that time I shall by<lb/> all means raise the
                money, &amp; <sic>endeaver</sic> to the utmost<lb/> to comply, with this my
                promise.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I shall also urge those, who are in <sic>arrea.</sic> for the<lb/> subscription for
                the <sic>occident</sic>.</p>
            <p>With the sincere wish for your uninterrupted<lb/> welfare &amp; Happiness I
                remain</p>
            <p>Dear sir<lb/> your true &amp; sincere Friend</p>
            <p><add>Hebrew</add>
                <persName role="author">B M Emanuel</persName>.</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Paid 10</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Rev: <hi rend="underline">Isaac</hi>
                <hi rend="underline"><addressee>Leeser</addressee></hi></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>
                    <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                </placeName>
            </p>
